Learnings:
    Q: Why scripts not inside app/ folder?
    A: Because scripts are not part of runtime application code. They are used for development, testing, or deployment purposes. Keeping them outside of the app/ folder helps to maintain a clear separation between the application code and the supporting scripts, making the project structure cleaner and more organized.
        - APP can be treated as package and everything inside app/ is considered runtime application code.

